Author: René Bertin <rjvbertin@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Feb 28 20:22:35 2026 +0100

    Support offloaded IO mode
    
    A rather well-hidden option (--io_submit_mode=offload) makes it
    possible to use multiple queues (iodepth>1) with synchronous IO
    engines. Thus removing the need for parameter adaptation.
    
    Since it is absolutely not clear to me which approach gives the
    most comparable results for, say, a Q8T1 test between async and
    sync IO engines (i.e. Q8T1 vs. Q1T8 "direct mode" or Q8T1 vs.
    Q8T1 "offload mode"), I decided to support both by adding the
    choice directly in the IO Engine submenu.
    NB: offload mode should not be used with async. engines, so that
    choice was easy to make.
    
    This also adds support for the "vsync" engine.
    
    Committed from host : Bola

